Short-term memory

Purpose:
- Active short-term and startup continuity memory for the current MemoryEndpoints.com work.

Last verified: 2026-07-09
Memory scope: current working facts, near-term direction, and offline fallback.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: update this file for active startup facts; append completed work to `.uai/progress.uai`; submit public-safe durable summaries to https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit when authenticated.
Source of truth: `.uai/totem.uai`, current repository state, user objective, and verified command output.
Next action for agents: keep local `.uai` active even when hosted MATM is available.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, or raw one-time keys.

2026-07-09:
- Workspace cloned from MichaelKappel/Multi-Agent-Memory.
- Initial implementation target is file-backed MATM with docs-backed durable memory.
- Database credentials exist outside repo in E:\ftp_Deploy.txt; values must remain redacted.
- MultiAgentMemory.com is the GitHub companion documentation site.
- MemoryEndpoints.com is the real endpoint site and live mid-to-long-term MATM memory boundary.
- Totem invariant: local `.uai` stays active always. If MemoryEndpoints.com is unreachable, agents continue from `.uai` instead of losing context.
- Use `.uai/` files for short-term/startup memory; use MemoryEndpoints.com MATM routes for mid-to-long-term memory when reachable and authenticated.
- MATM memory update URL for this repo: https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit
- Requested UAIX wizard/spec anchors to add: https://uaix.org/en-us/tools/ai-memory-package-wizard/#setup-MATM and https://uaix.org/en-us/tools/ai-memory-package-wizard/#setup-file-handoff-MATM
